# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]
- Planned improvements:
  - Add async version of the agent as an advanced optional module.
  - Add optional vector database integration (Chroma or FAISS).
  - Add PDF and DOCX parsing to the file parser tool.
  - Add a custom search API integration example (e.g., Tavily or SerpAPI).
  - Provide prebuilt deployment examples (Fly.io, Render, AWS ECS).

## [0.2.0] - 2025-02-01
### Changed
- Repositioned and renamed the project to **Self-Hosted AI Assistant Backend (FastAPI + LangChain)**.
- Updated API metadata (title and description) to reflect internal-tools and self-hosted positioning.
- Clarified project scope to emphasise backend service foundations rather than a learning-focused starter kit.

### Documentation
- Updated README to remove "starter kit" framing.
- Added explicit "What this is / isnâ€™t" section to avoid misinterpretation.

## [0.1.0] - 2025-01-15 (Initial release as FastAPI + LangChain LLM Agent Starter Kit)
### Added
- Initial release of the **FastAPI + LangChain LLM Agent Starter Kit**.
- Fully working sync LangChain agent with:
  - Calculator tool  
  - Web search stub  
  - File parser  
- FastAPI API endpoints:
  - `/health`
  - `/agent/invoke`
- Dockerfile and docker-compose configuration.
- Pydantic `.env` configuration system.
- GitHub Actions CI pipeline.
- Virtual environment setup instructions.
- Architecture diagram and Quickstart section.
- MIT License.
